TITLE: Defining a Basic User Type with ArkType in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define a simple User type using ArkType's 'type' function. It includes string, union, and optional array properties, and shows how to extract the TypeScript type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/arktypeio/arktype/blob/main/ark/docs/content/docs/intro/your-first-type.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { type } from "arktype"

const User = type({
	name: "string",
	platform: "'android' | 'ios'",
	"versions?": "(number | string)[]"
})

// extract the type if needed
type User = typeof User.infer
```

