TITLE: Customizing Complete Error Messages with Path Information
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the 'message' option to completely customize error messages including the path at which the error occurred, providing more context for nested validation errors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/arktypeio/arktype/blob/main/ark/docs/content/docs/configuration/index.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const User = type({
	password: "string >= 8"
}).configure({
	message: ctx =>
		`${ctx.propString || "(root)"}: ${ctx.actual} isn't ${ctx.expected}`
})
// ArkErrors: (root): a string isn't an object
const out1 = User("ez123")
// `.configure` only applies shallowly, so the nested error isn't changed!
// ArkErrors: password must be at least length 8 (was 5)
const out2 = User({ password: "ez123" })
```

