TITLE: Creating a Configured Scope in ArkType
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a configured scope in ArkType where configurations apply to all Types parsed within that scope, including custom error messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/arktypeio/arktype/blob/main/ark/docs/content/docs/configuration/index.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const myScope = scope(
	{ User: { age: "number < 100" } },
	{
		max: {
			actual: () => "unacceptably large"
		}
	}
)
const types = myScope.export()
// ArkErrors: age must be less than 100 (was unacceptably large)
types.User({ name: "Alice", age: 101 })
const parsedAfter = myScope.type({
	age: "number <= 100"
})
// ArkErrors: age must be at most 100 (was unacceptably large)
parsedAfter({ age: 101 })
```

