TITLE: Input Narrowing and Property Matching with in and at Methods
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using specialized match methods for input narrowing and property-based matching. Uses the .in<T>() method to specify the TypeScript type, and .at() to match based on a specific property (in this case, discriminating by 'id').
SOURCE: https://github.com/arktypeio/arktype/blob/main/ark/docs/content/docs/match.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// @errors: 2345
import { match } from "arktype"

type Data =
	| {
			id: 1
			oneValue: number
	  }
	| {
			id: 2
			twoValue: string
	  }

const discriminateValue = match
	// .in allows you to specify the input TypeScript allows for your matcher
	.in<Data>()
	// .at allows you to specify a key at which your input will be matched
	.at("id")
	.match({
